    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper discusses limma's empirical Bayes procedure and hyperparameter estimation in general terms (e.g., 'facilitate accurate estimate of the prior degrees of freedom determining the optimal amount of squeezing to be applied to the variances' in passage 11), but does not provide detailed mathematical exposition of HOW limma estimates hyperparameters. The research question focuses on hyperparameter estimation methodology, which is mentioned but not deeply explained in the passages. The paper's primary focus is on voom's mean-variance modeling and precision weights, not on limma's internal hyperparameter estimation algorithm.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does limma estimate hyperparameters of the prior distribution over gene-wise variances to compute moderated t-statistics and B-statistics?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:26.969490+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "voom: variance modeling at the observation-level... Our strategy is to estimate non-parametrically the mean-variance trend of the logged read counts and to use this mean-variance relationship to predict the variance of each log-cpm value. The predicted variance is then encapsulated as an inverse weight for the log-cpm value.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the voom precision-weight computation algorithm in detail, including LOWESS fitting and inverse variance weighting.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct voom precision-weight computation for RNA-seq count data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:26.969490+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "limma is central to the voom methodology and is used throughout the paper for differential expression analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "limma",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:26.969490+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The results presented in this article were obtained using R version 3.0.0 and the software packages limma 3.16.2, edgeR 3.2.3, baySeq 1.14.1, DESeq 1.12.0, DSS 1.4.0, PoissonSeq 1.1.2 and tweeDEseqCountData 1.0.8.",
      "asbval:note": "R is explicitly stated as the programming environment used for all analyses.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "R",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:26.969490+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The table shows output from the limma topTable function. As well as gene ID and symbol, columns give chromosome location (Chr), log2-fold-change (logFC), average log2 expression (AveExpr), moderated t, P value, false discovery rate and B-statistic for each gene.",
      "asbval:note": "Table 1 in the paper exemplifies exactly this output format with gene identifiers, logFC, moderated t-statistics, P values, FDR, and B-statistics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
