    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The above linear model is fitted, by ordinary least squares, to the log-cpm values ygi for each gene. This yields regression coefficient estimates \u03b2^g, fitted values \u03bc^gi=xiT\u03b2^g and residual standard deviations sg.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms lmFit produces coefficient estimates and fitted values. However, the paper does not explicitly name the output object type as 'MArrayLM' nor does it explicitly mention 'standard errors' or 'design matrix information' as outputs. The paper describes the mathematical outputs but not the R object class or all structural components claimed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
