      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_002/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses limma's empirical Bayes procedure and eBayes function, but the title claims the task is to 'reconstruct' the computation of moderated t-statistics. The paper describes using eBayes as part of the pipeline but does not present a task focused on reconstructing or deriving the eBayes computation itself. The paper applies eBayes rather than reconstructing it.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct empirical Bayes moderated t-statistic computation via limma's eBayes",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:40.295167+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card frames the task around applying lmFit to 'a microarray dataset', but the paper's primary focus is applying lmFit to RNA-seq log-cpm data via the voom method. While lmFit is used in both contexts, the paper does not emphasize microarray application.",
        "The title suggests a reconstruction or derivation task ('Reconstruct empirical Bayes moderated t-statistic computation'), but the paper demonstrates application of existing limma functions rather than reconstruction of the underlying statistical computation.",
        "The card does not mention voom, which is the central methodological contribution of the paper and the primary context in which lmFit is applied in this work."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:40.295167+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1093_nar_gkv007__task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For our simulations, there are no compositional differences between the libraries so there should be no need to estimate compositional normalization factors. For this reason we did not use the calcNormFactors function with edgeR or estimateSizeFactors with DESeq or estNormFactors with DSS. This should tend to improve the performance of the packages and to make them more comparable, as any differences between the packages can be attributed to the statistical procedures rather than to differences between the normalization strategies.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states they did NOT use calcNormFactors in their simulations, and discusses compositional normalization as optional. The paper does mention TMM-scale normalization was used in some real data analyses (e.g., Nigerian lymphoblastoid cell lines, Drosophila), but the research question as framed (comparing calcNormFactors-prepended voom vs. limma-only) is not directly addressed. The paper compares voom vs. count-based methods and discusses normalization options, but does not perform the specific comparison requested in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Does prepending edgeR's calcNormFactors normalization to the limma voom pipeline alter the ranked list of differentially expressed genes compared to the standard limma-only workflow?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:06:54.024998+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
