      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/design-matrix-construction-experiments/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We use linear models to describe how the treatment factors are assigned to the different RNA samples. We assume that: E(ygi)=\u03bcgi=xiT\u03b2g where xi is a vector of covariates and \u03b2g is a vector of unknown coefficients representing log2-fold-changes between experimental conditions. In matrix terms: E(yg)=X\u03b2g where yg is the vector of log-cpm values for gene g and X is the design matrix with the xi as rows.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the design matrix X and its role in specifying the linear model structure for differential expression analysis.",
