    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/design-matrix-construction-experiments/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Gene expression profiling is one of the most commonly used genomic techniques in biological research... This includes methods for differential expression analysis [1-3], random effects [4,5], gene set enrichment [6], gene set testing [7,8] and so on. One popular differential expression pipeline is that provided by the limma software package [9]. The limma pipeline includes linear modeling to analyze complex experiments with multiple treatment factors...",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the use of linear models for differential expression analysis with multiple treatment factors, which aligns with the scope claim.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "design-matrix-construction-experiments",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have microarray or RNA-seq expression data paired with phenotype/sample metadata describing experimental conditions, treatments, or group assignments, and you need to fit a linear model to test for differential expression across those conditions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:35.006317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/design-matrix-construction-experiments/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The above linear model is fitted, by ordinary least squares, to the log-cpm values ygi for each gene... In matrix terms: E(yg)=X\u03b2g where yg is the vector of log-cpm values for gene g and X is the design matrix with the xi as rows.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that the design matrix X is a required input to the linear modeling pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "design-matrix-construction-experiments",
