    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... The limma pipeline includes linear modeling to analyze complex experiments with multiple treatment factors, quantitative weights to account for variations in precision between different observations, and empirical Bayes statistical methods to borrow strength between genes. Borrowing information between genes is a crucial feature of the genome-wide statistical methods, as it allows for gene-specific variation while still providing reliable inference with small sample sizes.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes empirical Bayes methods for borrowing strength between genes and improving inference with small sample sizes. The voom method feeds into limma's empirical Bayes pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply empirical Bayes moderation via eBayes to stabilize variance estimates across genes after fitting a linear model to normalized expression data. This shrinks per-gene variance estimates toward a common value, improving statistical power and ranking reliability especially when",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:52.465674+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One popular differential expression pipeline is that provided by the limma software package [9]. The limma pipeline includes linear modeling to analyze complex experiments with multiple treatment factors, quantitative weights to account for variations in precision between different observations, and empirical Bayes statistical methods to borrow strength between genes.",
      "asbval:note": "limma is confirmed as providing linear modeling and empirical Bayes methods. The paper also mentions 'limma's empirical Bayes procedure' and 'limma's standard differential expression pipeline' throughout.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "limma provides lmFit and eBayes functions for linear model fitting and empirical Bayes moderation of variance estimates",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:52.465674+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... Our strategy is to estimate non-parametrically the mean-variance trend of the logged read counts and to use this mean-variance relationship to predict the variance of each log-cpm value. The predicted variance is then encapsulated as an inverse weight for the log-cpm value. When the weights are incorporated into a linear modeling procedure, the mean-variance relationship in the log-cpm values is effectively eliminated.",
      "asbval:note": "voom is explicitly described as generating precision weights that account for the mean-variance relationship and feeding into limma's pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "voom precision-weighted normalization prior to lmFit; produces precision weights that account for mean-variance relationship in RNA-seq",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:52.465674+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The results presented in this article were obtained using R version 3.0.0 and the software packages limma 3.16.2, edgeR 3.2.3, baySeq 1.14.1, DESeq 1.12.0, DSS 1.4.0, PoissonSeq 1.1.2 and tweeDEseqCountData 1.0.8. All of these packages are part of the Bioconductor project [67,68]... The voom methodology proposed in the article is implemented in the voom function of the limma package.",
      "asbval:note": "R is confirmed as the execution environment for limma and voom functions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "R execution environment for limma eBayes",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:52.465674+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Library sizes were scale-normalized by the TMM method [54] using edgeR software [12] prior to the voom analysis... TMM-scale normalization [54] was used for all the analysis methods, except for DESeq and PoissonSeq, which have their own built-in normalization methods.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper uses edgeR for TMM normalization (via calcNormFactors function, though not explicitly named in these passages). However, edgeR is used as a normalization tool prior to voom/limma analysis, not as a primary tool for the empirical Bayes moderation task itself. The card lists edgeR as a tool for this task, but the paper's primary focus is on limma's eBayes for moderation. edgeR is used for normalization preprocessing, which is a supporting role rather than the core eBayes moderation role claimed in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-empirical-bayes-moderation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "edgeR with calcNormFactors [TMM normalization]",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:08:52.465674+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/differential-expression-result-interpretation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... The limma pipeline includes linear modeling to analyze complex experiments with multiple treatment factors, quantitative weights to account for variations in precision between different observations, and empirical Bayes statistical methods to borrow strength between genes... The normal-based empirical Bayes statistical procedures can adapt to different types of datasets and can provide exact type I error rate control even for experiments with a small number of replicate samples.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes empirical Bayes shrinkage of variance estimates and demonstrates type I error control with small sample sizes. B-statistics are mentioned in results tables (Table 1) as posterior log-odds of differential expression.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "differential-expression-result-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Empirical Bayesian shrinkage of gene-wise variance estimates to compute moderated t-statistics and B-statistics that remain stable even with small sample sizes, enabling robust ranking and significance assessment of differential expression.",
