    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/method-comparison-differential-calls/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This article compares the performance of the limma-based pipelines to edgeR [20,34], DESeq [13], baySeq [21], TSPM [25], PoissonSeq [26] and DSS [22]... Simulation studies show that the limma pipelines perform at least as well in terms of power and error rate control as the NB or Poisson methods... voom and limma-trend perform almost equally well when the sequencing depths are the same for each RNA sample. When the sequencing depths are different, voom is the clear best performer.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper directly compares multiple pipelines and evaluates how methodological choices (normalization, precision weighting) affect differential expression results and gene rankings.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "method-comparison-differential-calls",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compare ranked lists of differentially expressed genes across two analysis pipelines (e.g., TMM-normalized voom versus limma-only, or different normalization strategies) to quantify how methodological choices affect differential expression calls, gene rankings, and statistical si",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:21.665206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/method-comparison-differential-calls/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We found that variation in sequencing depth between libraries had a noticeable impact on some RNA-seq analysis methods... voom shows consistent performance in all scenarios... When the library sizes are unequal, voom is the clear best performer.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates that normalization and preprocessing choices (library size handling, TMM normalization) materially affect downstream conclusions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "method-comparison-differential-calls",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential when evaluating whether upstream normalization or preprocessing steps meaningfully alter downstream biological conclusions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:21.665206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/method-comparison-differential-calls/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... The log-cpm values ygi and associated weights wgj are then input into limma's standard linear modeling and empirical Bayes differential expression analysis pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes limma's role in fitting linear models and empirical Bayes procedures; topTable function mentioned in results section for extracting ranked gene lists.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "method-comparison-differential-calls",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "limma: Fits linear models (lmFit) and applies empirical Bayes moderation (eBayes) for each pipeline; extracts ranked gene lists (topTable) for comparison",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:21.665206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/method-comparison-differential-calls/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Library sizes were scale-normalized by the TMM method [54] using edgeR software [12] prior to the voom analysis... The different count-based packages implement different methods of compositional normalization [54].",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly uses edgeR's TMM normalization (calcNormFactors) prior to voom analysis in multiple case studies.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
