    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes empirical Bayes procedures in limma for stabilizing variance estimates and computing moderated statistics for differential expression.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute moderated t-statistics and B-statistics for differential expression by applying empirical Bayes hyperparameter estimation to stabilize gene-wise variance estimates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:54.287544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Borrowing information between genes is a crucial feature of the genome-wide statistical methods, as it allows for gene-specific variation while still providing reliable inference with small sample sizes. The normal-based empirical Bayes statistical procedures can adapt to different types of datasets and can provide exact type I error rate control even for experiments with a small number of replicate samples.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states empirical Bayes methods provide reliable inference with small sample sizes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential when analyzing gene expression data with small sample sizes, where ordinary t-statistics are unstable.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:54.287544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline. This opens access for RNA-seq analysts to a large body of methodology developed for microarrays.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates application to microarray and RNA-seq data. qPCR and proteomics are not explicitly mentioned in the passages; scope is narrower than claimed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have a fitted linear model (lmFit object) from microarray, RNA-seq, qPCR, or proteomics data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:54.287544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The B-statistic is the posterior log-odds of differential expression.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms B-statistic is log-odds of differential expression and emphasizes small sample performance.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it especially when sample size is small and you need both moderated t-statistics (for hypothesis testing) and B-statistics (log-odds of differential expression).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:54.287544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One popular differential expression pipeline is that provided by the limma software package [9]. The limma pipeline includes linear modeling to analyze complex experiments with multiple treatment factors, quantitative weights to account for variations in precision between different observations, and empirical Bayes statistical methods to borrow strength between genes.",
      "asbval:note": "limma package explicitly provides empirical Bayes methods; eBayes function is mentioned in Materials and methods section.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "limma R package providing eBayes function for empirical Bayes hyperparameter estimation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:10:54.287544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/moderated-t-statistic-computation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The above linear model is fitted, by ordinary least squares, to the log-cpm values ygi for each gene. This yields regression coefficient estimates \u03b2^g, fitted values \u03bc^gi=xiT\u03b2^g and residual standard deviations sg.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes linear model fitting within limma pipeline; lmFit is the standard limma function for this purpose (mentioned in Materials and methods).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "moderated-t-statistic-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
