      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The different count-based packages implement different methods of compositional normalization [54]. For this reason we did not use the calcNormFactors function with edgeR",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms edgeR's calcNormFactors function exists and is used for compositional normalization (which includes TMM), but does not explicitly describe DGEList objects or detail how scale factors are stored. The function name and general role are confirmed, but implementation details are not provided in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "edgeR: Computes TMM normalization factors via calcNormFactors and creates DGEList objects to store count matrices and per-sample scale factors",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... The log-cpm values and associated weights are then input into limma's standard differential expression pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes voom generating precision weights and entering them into limma's empirical Bayes pipeline. The functions lmFit and eBayes are standard limma functions referenced in the context of linear modeling and empirical Bayes procedures, though not all named explicitly in these passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "limma: Applies voom to generate precision weights from normalized library sizes and mean-variance estimates; fits linear models with lmFit; applies empirical Bayes shrinkage with eBayes",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The voom method estimates the mean-variance relationship of the log-counts, generates a precision weight for each observation and enters these into the limma empirical Bayes analysis pipeline... We work with log-counts normalized for sequence depth, specifically with log-counts per million (log-cpm).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms voom works with log-cpm and generates precision weights accounting for mean-variance relationship. However, the paper does not explicitly state that voom requires or operates on TMM-normalized input. The paper uses TMM normalization in some case studies but voom itself is described as working with log-cpm values after normalization by sequencing depth, not specifically TMM-normalized counts.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "voom: Transforms TMM-normalized counts to log2-CPM scale with precision weights that account for mean-variance relationship, enabling linear modeling on normalized RNA-seq data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The results presented in this article were obtained using R version 3.0.0 and the software packages limma 3.16.2, edgeR 3.2.3, baySeq 1.14.1, DESeq 1.12.0, DSS 1.4.0, PoissonSeq 1.1.2 and tweeDEseqCountData 1.0.8.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly confirms R as the execution environment for limma and edgeR packages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "R: Execution environment for edgeR and limma workflows",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The different count-based packages implement different methods of compositional normalization [54]. For our simulations, there are no compositional differences between the libraries so there should be no need to estimate compositional normalization factors.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper acknowledges compositional normalization methods exist and are used when compositional differences are present, but does not provide detailed guidance on when to apply TMM specifically. The claim is semantically consistent with the paper's discussion but not explicitly detailed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply TMM normalization when you have raw RNA-seq read counts from multiple samples and suspect differences in library composition (e.g., one sample over-represents a highly-expressed gene or transcript class relative to others).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not discuss the interaction between TMM normalization and voom's mean-variance modeling, nor does it explain how composition bias specifically distorts the mean-variance relationship in voom. The paper uses TMM in some analyses with voom but does not explain the mechanistic relationship claimed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2014-15-2-r29",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization-tmm",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This is especially critical before combining normalization with limma's voom precision-weighting, where composition bias can distort the mean-variance relationship and downstream fold-change rankings.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:11:37.435328+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
